<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Falling Ice,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Worker's Car Crushed By Falling Chunk Of Ice</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LODI, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 2-foot-long slab of ice fell from a
2,000-foot-high plane and crushed a car, authorities said. No
injuries were reported.
   No other details were available about the plane involved in
Monday's incident, said Federal Aviation Administration spokesman
Peter Nelson, who noted that about 600 planes fly daily over the
area to Newark Airport.
   Workers at the Penske GM Power Co. plant said they heard a thump
and when they looked outside, saw the chunk of blue ice on the roof
of employee Charles Reid's car.
   Reid said he recently spent $1,400 on a new engine for his 1979
Ford and joked that his insurance company would never believe what
had happened.
