<HEAD>Roman Numerals Are in With This Administration</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan's nominee to be secretary of
the Navy, William L. Ball III, is just one more reason to see
triple when looking at the administration.
   A look through the directory of top government officials shows
that this administration doesn't take a back seat to anybody in the
Roman numeral department.
   At the Pentagon: Frank C. Carlucci III, secretary of defense; H.
Lawrence Garrett III, undersecretary of the Navy.
   At the Treasury Department, James A. Baker III, secretary.
   At the Office of Management and Budget: James C. Miller III,
director; L. Wayne Arny III, assistant director for national
security.
   At the Commerce Department: Orson G. Swindle III, assistant
secretary for economic development.
   At the Justice Department: Edwin Meese III, attorney general.
   At the Interstate Commerce Commission: J.J. Simmons III,
commissioner.
   In addition, the list shows Charles Tyroler II of the
Intelligence Oversight Board; J. Curtis Mack II, assistant
secretary of commerce for the National Oceanic and Atmospheric
Administration; Lt. Col, Claudius Watts II, comptroller of the
Department of the Air Force; and Wendell L. Willkie II, general
counsel of the Department of Education.
   They are all pikers, however, compared with Carlucci's deputy,
William H. Taft IV, and Transportation Secretary James H. Burnley
IV.
