<HEAD>Tally For One Precinct Missing In South Dakota</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIOUX FALLS, S.D. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The returns from South Dakota's
presidential primary election were complete _ except for Lincoln
No. 51, a rural precinct near Lemmon in extreme northwestern South
Dakota.
   Fern Brockel, Perkins County auditor, said election workers in
the precinct were supposed to fill in the vote totals for each
candidate on the unofficial return sheet. But she said it was given
to her with all the lines blank.
   The returns are in the official poll book, but under the rules,
it cannot be opened until the official canvass this afternoon.
   Without the missing precinct, Perkins County residents cast
1,345 votes out of the nearly 165,000 votes cast in the election.
