<HEAD>Cook Protests Official Feasting by Upending Banquet Table</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   China's latest activist in the campaign against
high-living officials is a cook who overturned a banquet table in
disgust over their feasting.
   The official China Daily said today the unidentified woman cook
was applauded by residents in Linshu County, one of the poorest in
the coastal province of Shandong.
   It said she was angry at the county Communist Party secretary,
who together with other officials last December gathered for a
meeting which in actuality was a 14-dish banquet.
   The party said county officials were already under fire for
investing $378,000 to build a guest house for VIPs and budgeting
$59,000 for banquets last year at the county government guesthouse.
   China's State Council, or Cabinet, last year ordered all party
and government officials to cut back on banqueting and gift-giving.
