<HEAD>Children's Death Toll From Whooping Cough Reaches 12</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LA PLATA, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The death toll in a monthlong
outbreak of whooping cough reached 12 with the death of an infant
girl, health authorities said.
   The 2-year-old girl died Friday in the Maria Ludovica Children's
Hospital in Buenos Aires despite a campaign by public health
authorities to innoculate children in the Buenos Aires-La Plata
area.
   Whooping cough normally is not a common health risk in Argentina.
   Officials have noted each of 12 fatalities were malnourished,
came from low-income families and had not been innoculated against
whooping cough.
