<HEAD>Taiwan Residents Made 90,000 Trips To China Last Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Taiwan residents made nearly 90,000 trips to
China in 1987, an official report said. It was a huge increase from
the previous year and was brought about by Taiwan's lifting of a
ban on such travel.
   China's domestic China News Service, in a report appearing in
Hong Kong today, said ``Taiwan compatriots'' traveled to the
Chinese mainland more than 89,000 times last year, a 180 percent
increase from 1986. The statistics were provided by a Public
Security Bureau spokesman, the report said.
   The Nationalist Chinese government on Taiwan in October lifted a
38-year old ban on travel to mainland China to allow family
reunions. Thousands of Taiwan residents secretly traveled to China
before the ban was lifted.
</TEXT>
