<2ND_LINE>PM-Panda Killers,0172</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Panda Killers Get Up to Life in Prison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eleven men were given prison terms ranging from
three years to life for killing two giant pandas, the official
Xinhua News Agency said today.
   The report said a court in northwest Sichuan province, one of
the last natural habitats of the endangered species, found the men
guilty in two separate incidents of killing the pandas and selling
their pelts.
   It did not say how many of the men were given life terms.
   In December, another court in Sichuan sentenced 26 men to prison
terms ranging from two years to life for killing six pandas and
selling their skins.
   Only about 1,000 giant pandas still survive in the wild, all in
Sichuan and neighboring southwest China provinces.
   Although the Chinese government has banned panda hunting, the
pandas' numbers are believed to have decreased as a result of their
low fertility rate, a shortage of the wild bamboo on which they
feed and human predators.
</TEXT>
