<HEAD>Singer Alice Cooper Says He is Write-In Candidate for Governor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shock-rock star Alice Cooper, who says he
bought his first car years ago from impeached Arizona Gov. Evan
Mecham, has half-serious plans to run for political office in his
home state.
   ``I'm definitely a write-in candidate,'' said the Phoenix-born
singer. ``Hey, I'm a native. I'm a registered voter. I represent
