<FILEID>AP-NR-02-24-88 2212EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-MousketeerSearch     02-24 0133</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Mousketeer Search,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Disney Seeks Mouseketeer Lookalikes for Movie</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It must be Friday because the Disney Channel
is looking for youngsters who look like the original Mousketeers
for a movie about the start of ``The Mickey Mouse Club'' in 1955.
   On the syndicated show, which lasted until 1959, Friday was
``Talent Roundup Day.''
   The producers are looking for kids who look like Annette
Funicello, Darlene Gillespie, Tommy Cole and all the other original
Mousketeers.
   The search begins Friday in Dallas, goes to Radio City Music
Hall in New York on March 5, to Chicago on March 19 and Los Angeles
on March 26. Parents can also send their children's photos to
Mousketeer Casting, Disney Studios, 500 S. Buena Vista, Burbank,
Calif., 91521.
   Let's hear it _ ``M-I-C-K-E-Y M-O-U-S-E!''
