<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BaptistHeadquarters     02-24 0183</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Baptist Headquarters,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Baptist Group Announces Construction Of Headquarters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The world's largest black religious
organization will begin construction in March on its world center
headquarters, church officials announced Wednesday.
   The $9.2 million development for the National Baptist Convention
U.S.A. Inc. is expected to be completed in April 1989, said T.J.
Jemison, president of the organization.
   More than 40,000 convention members are expected to attend
dedication ceremonies two months later, he said.
   ``With 7.7 million members, the National Baptist Convention has
grown to the point where the leadership decided we need a central
headquarters from which to manage our many missions,'' Jemison said.
   ``The six boards which now comprise the convention are currently
located throughout the country, and to bring them all under one
roof will result in a fundamental restructuring of our entire
organization from which we should reap tremendous benefits,'' he
said.
   The 75,000-square-foot building, containing a 2,000-seat chapel
and crowned by a 225-foot spire, will be built on 12.5 acres near
the seminary of the National Baptist Convention and the Southern
Baptist Convention in downtown Nashville.
</TEXT>
