   The conference maintained the group, Abortion Rights
Mobilization, has no standing to attack the church's tax exemption,
and that allowing it would invite similar challenges to all
reglious bodies by political opponents.
   The group wants the IRS to revoke tax exemption of the church's
functions, national and local _ thousands of parishes, schools,
hospitals, religious orders and other agencies _ on grounds the
church engaged in political activity against abortion.
</TEXT>
