<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-BritishBank     02-24 0344</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-British Bank,0355</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Barclays' Profit Plummets 70 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Barclays Bank PLC, one of Britain's four major
commercial banks, said Wednesday that its 1987 profit plummeted
70.8 percent, largely because it raised its provisions for loans to
Latin American and other countries.
   Barclays said it earned 185 million pounds, or $327 million last
year, compared with 633 million pounds, or $1.12 billion, in 1986.
Included in the 1986 figure was a one-time gain of 21 million
pounds, or $37 million, from the disposal of certain assets.
   On a per-share basis, that works out to 25.8 pence, or 46 cents,
a share, vs. 88.9 pence, or $1.57, a share in the previous year.
   Last summer, Barclays raised its provisions against loans to
lesser developed countries to 30 percent of its total loans
outstanding, then increased that stake at the end of the year.
   As of Dec. 31, its total provisions stood at 716 million pounds,
or $1.27 billion _ 35 percent of the bank's total 2.026 billion
pounds, or $3.59 billion, outstanding.
   ``The results achieved in our group operations through the year
reflect a credible performance,'' said Chairman John Quinton.
``Even though we decided to recognize the further deterioration in
the quality of LDC debt by making further provisions, the impact on
our capital has been comfortably absorbed.''
   Barclays de Zoete Wedd, the bank's investment banking
subsidiary, reported a loss of 11 million pounds, or $19 million,
for the year, compared with a profit of 1 million pounds, or $1.77
million, the year before.
   Barclays said the unit was profitable up to October and in the
final two months of the year, but that trading losses suffered
during the crash pushed it into the red.
   The unit announced last November that it lost 50 million pounds,
or $89 million, during the crash.
   Profits from Barclays' U.S. unit were hurt by the fall of the
dollar.
   The bank said profit grew 14 percent in dollar terms, but only
1.6 percent in terms of pounds _ to 64 million pounds, compared
with 63 million.
</TEXT>
