<HEAD>London Shares Edge Higher</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with trading activity, closing
index; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices edged higher in thin trading
Wednesday, bringing an end to a strong two-day advance.
   Dealers attributed the session's dullness to a lack of
market-affecting news and uninspiring performances on Wall Street
on Tuesday and early Wednesday.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed 2.2
points, or 0.1 percent, higher at 1,760.1.
   Volume declined to a light 338.1 million shares from 474.1
million shares traded Tuesday.
   Dealers said business was slack as many investors waited for
Monday's data on Britain's balance of payments for January. They
also were waiting for Thursday's announcement of fourth-quarter
earnings from Imperial Chemical Industries PLC. The giant chemical
company's earnings are viewed as an unofficial indicator of the
state of British industry, dealers said.
</TEXT>
