<HEAD>Weekly Petroleum Review</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Total crude oil runs to stills averaged
12,695,000 barrels daily during the week ended Friday, Feb. 19, the
American Petroleum Institute reported Wednesday. This compared with
12,739,000 barrels daily in the previous week and 12,199,000
barrels daily a year ago.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 10,243,000 barrels daily
compared with 10,330,000 the previous week and 9,749,000 a year ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to
6,760,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,641,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 6,406,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 5,677,000 a day
compared with 5,552,000 a day last week and 5,300,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
240,493,000 barrels, versus 236,560,000 a week earlier and
252,947,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 207,918,000
barrels, compared with 203,396,000 in the previous week and
221,181,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production
for the week ended Friday was 8,182,000 barrels compared with
8,320,000 last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 333,084,000 barrels at the close of
last week, against 334,964,000 a week previous and 328,680,000 a
year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 250,753,000 barrels,
compared with 251,609,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 3,913,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 706,000,
distillate fuel oil, 314,O00, and others 1,173,000, a total of
6,106,000 barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 172,000 barrels, and products
72,000, a total of 244,000 barrels, for a grand total of 6,350,000.
   For the four weeks, daily imports east of California were crude
oil 4,355,000 barrels, residual fuel oil 322,000, distillate fuel
oil 130,000, and others 625,000, for a total of 5,432,000 barrels.
   For the four weeks, California daily imports averaged for crude
oil 180,000 barrels, products 55,000, a total of 235,000 barrels,
for a grand total of 5,667,000 barrels.
