<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-Litton     02-24 0165</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Litton,0171</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Litton Net Up 19 Percent in Second Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Litton Industries Inc. said
Wednesday its net earnings rose 19 percent in the second quarter,
mainly because of improvements in its resource-exploration and
industrial-automation units.
   The high-technology conglomerate netted $40.7 million, or $1.56
a share, for the three months ended Jan. 31, up from $34.1 million,
or $1.28 a share, a year earlier.
   Revenue for the second quarter rose 19.6 percent, to $1.16
billion from $974.5 million.
   Litton's profit also rose 19 percent in the half. The company
earned $81.3 million, or $3.07 a share, up from $68.4 million, or
$2.54 a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 15.2 percent, to $2.35
billion from $2.04 billion.
   Litton's biggest improvement was in the resource-exploration and
industrial-automation units of its industrial systems and services
division, in part because of acquisitions. For the half, earnings
for the division jumped 183 percent to $65.7 million and revenue
rose 78.5 percent to $775.3 million.
</TEXT>
